I created my digital literacy infographic using Canva because it provides simple tools and ready templates. My design explains the concept of digital literacy and its importance for students. It includes key topics such as useful digital tools, safe internet practices, email etiquette, and professional online presence. The goal of the infographic is to help students understand how to use the internet in a safe, responsible, and effective way.

I used short points and a clean layout so the content is easy to read and understand. I also added sections to highlight important areas like online safety and communication. One challenge I faced was organizing all the information without making the design look crowded. I learned how to balance content and design by keeping text minimal and using proper spacing. This task helped me understand how visual communication improves learning and makes information more engaging.
